While researching cybercrime, what surprised me most was how easily people fall victim to simple tricks such as fake links and urgent payment requests.

Many scams do not involve complex hacking; instead, they rely on manipulating human emotions like fear, urgency, or trust. 

I also learned that even educated users and students are frequently targeted, especially through UPI and social media platforms. This made me realize that awareness is just as important as technology in preventing cybercrime.


One habit I will personally change is being more careful before clicking any link or approving payment requests. I will always verify the sender and read details properly before taking action.
 
I will also avoid sharing OTPs or personal information under any circumstances. 

Additionally, I plan to enable stronger security features like app locks and regularly monitor my bank transactions. 

These small precautions can significantly reduce the risk of cyber fraud and help me stay safe online.
